TITLE: Testing Vim Star Command with Neovim Backed Tests in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to test Zed's Vim emulation against Neovim behavior using the NeovimBackedTestContext. The example tests the '*' command in visual mode, verifying that Zed's implementation matches Neovim's behavior when searching for the selected text.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zed-industries/zed/blob/main/crates/vim/README.md#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[gpui::test]
async fn test_visual_star_hash(cx: &mut gpui::TestAppContext) {
    let mut cx = NeovimBackedTestContext::new(cx).await;

    cx.set_shared_state("Àáa.c. abcd a.c. abcd").await;
    cx.simulate_shared_keystrokes(["v", "3", "l", "*"]).await;
    cx.assert_shared_state("a.c. abcd Àáa.c. abcd").await;
